SIMPLE: decimation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decimation
<hw>Dec`i*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>decimatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧cimation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A tithing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>State
Trials (1630).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A selection of every tenth person by lot, as for
punishment.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The destruction of any large proportion, as of
people by pestilence or war.</def> <rj><au>Milman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decimator</ent>⟦br⟧
